Thank you for your recent application for the Junior Python Developer
position at Innovatech Solutions. We were very impressed with your resume
and would like to invite you for an initial interview to discuss your
skills and experience.

The interview will be held at our main office located at 123 Tech Avenue,
Silicon Valley, CA. We have a slot available for you next Tuesday.

The starting salary for this role is budgeted at $75,000 per year.

Please let us know if you are available.

Best regards, The Innovatech HR Team

________________________________
From: notifications@smartrecruiters.com <notifications@smartrecruiters.com> on behalf of Esther Louis from Publicis Sapient <notifications@smartrecruiters.com>
Sent: 09 November 2022 15:25
To: jeremy.ockenden@hotmail.co.uk <jeremy.ockenden@hotmail.co.uk>
Subject: Your Next Steps with Publicis Sapient – Data Assessment

​​​​​​​​​​

Hi Jeremy,

It was great talking with you today.

As mentioned on our call, the next step in the process is a coding test, to be completed by 15/11/2022

  *   You have 45 minutes to complete the test and you will shoot a small video of yourself for 3 mins at the end explaining your solution.
     *   1st coding question (45 min time limit)
  *   The test will be sent out from HireVue, our testing platform. Let me know if you have not received the email by tomorrow. Do not start the test until you are ready to complete it, there is no practice, when you click the red button “Practice or Take Assessment” it is taking you to the real assessment.
  *   Example of what you will see in your email:

                  [https://c.smartrecruiters.com/sr-company-images-prod/58822766e4b0680b1154ae69/f28746f3-c4c1-464b-aac6-bdd3f3ad17da/original?r=s3]

  *   You will need to use Google Chrome for the assessment, to be compatible with the screen-sharing functionality in HireVue.

Once you’ve completed the assessment, you will hear from us within 5 days on next steps. Please let me know if you have any questions.

I wish you all the best

Esther St Louis
